  "prompt": "Are there statutes that address money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several statutes that address money laundering, primarily at the federal level in the United States, but also internationally. Here's a breakdown:\n\n**United States:**\n\n*   **18 U.S.C. \u00a7 1956 (Laundering of Monetary Instruments):** This is the core federal money laundering statute. It prohibits:\n    *   Financial transactions involving the proceeds of specified unlawful activity (SUA) (also known as predicate offenses), with the intent to promote the SUA.\n    *   Financial transactions involving the proceeds of SUA, knowing that the property represents the proceeds of some form of unlawful activity, and intending to conceal or disguise the nature, location, source, ownership, or control of the proceeds.\n    *   Transporting, transmitting, or transferring monetary instruments or funds into or out of the United States with the intent to promote SUA or knowing that the funds represent the proceeds of some form of unlawful activity.\n*   **18",
